%N A393373 Decimal expansion of the weight factor for Hermite-Gauss quadrature of degree 7 corresponding to abscissa A393369.
%C A393373 There are floor(k/2) positive zeros of the Hermite polynomial of degree k:
%C A393373    k | zeros                           | corresponding weights for Hermite-Gauss quadrature
%C A393373   ---+---------------------------------+----------------------------------------------------
%C A393373    2 | A010503                         | A019704
%C A393373    3 | 0, A115754                      | 10*A019717, A019708
%C A393373    4 | A393353, A393354                | A393355, A393356
%C A393373    5 | 0, A393357, A393358             | A245887, A393360, A393361
%C A393373    6 | A393362, A393363, A393364       | A393365, A393366, A393367
%C A393373    7 | 0, A393368, A393369, A393370    | A393371, A393372, this sequence, A393374
